description:
&lt;p&gt;Community Diabetes Staff Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a permanent band 5, Community Diabetes Staff Nurse, to work alongside our team of Diabetes Specialist Nurses in the Southport &amp; Formby locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work primarily with community services to support patients who are new to injectable therapy. The aim is for the post holder to support patients to become independent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post provides a perfect opportunity for individuals who may have an interest in pursuing a career specialising in Diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small team and pride ourselves with excellent communication skills and providing support for each other. The Community Diabetes Team also work closely alongside the dietetic, podiatry and District Nursing services to ensure a holistic approach to working and this enables us to deliver the highest standard of care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated Staff Nurse who can demonstrate excellent clinical and interpersonal qualities. The successful candidate must be able to work independently and part of a team, have a positive outlook and ensure that delivering a high quality service, is a key priority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to work 08:30- 16:30, Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt; This post is subject to an enhanced DBS Clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angela Greenwood / Eileen Power / Dawn James on 01704 387270 or S&amp;FDiabetesSpecialistNurses@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
